properties.abstract: In winter the Chrbschhorn is a famous summit for ski tours. By bike it is a breathtaking tour with a high proportion of single trails.
properties.description:
From the Tourism and Sports Centre at Davos Platz the route begins by heading in the direction of Davos Dorf along the valley road (Talstrasse). At the river Schiabach we branch off to the left and begin the climb up to the Schatzalp. Initially the road is asphalted, but after crossing the promenade and reaching the last few houses, it becomes a wide track.

From the Schatzalp the track continues in the direction of Brschalp. After the Bschalp the trail becomes very steep. Before we reach the Hhenweg, we branch off to the left to reach the Strela Pass along the panoramic trail. The whole way you enjoy a wonderful view of the surrounding mountains of Davos. From the Strela Pass a wonderful single trail takes us across the Latschelfurgga to the Chrbschhorn hut. Anyone still fit enough at this stage has the opportunity to climb up to the summit of the Chrbschhorn on foot. The view is beautiful. 

After the Chrbschhorn hut comes the highlight of the tour. A technically demanding single trail downhill run to the Stafelalp. From the Stafelalp we finally return to Davos via Frauenkirch.
